../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:251:In CKN and Lin's reformulation, the key estimate has the form (using scale-invariant quantities Φ(r) ~ r^{−1}∫∫_{Q_r}|∇u|²):
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:257:Vasseur's transport terms give **5/3 > 3/2** (better than CKN), but the local pressure term gives **4/3 < 3/2** (worse, in the sense of being farther from full regularity). So:
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:259:- **Where De Giorgi hits a new wall:** local pressure (4/3 — a new obstruction not visible in CKN)
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:272:**No ε-absorption in the main iteration.** Unlike CKN (which uses Young's inequality with free ε to absorb gradient error terms from cutoffs), Vasseur's De Giorgi iteration uses **no free parameters in the core Proposition 3**. Every estimate is done with fixed universal constants. The only source of lossiness is:
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:280:### Comparison with CKN's ε-Absorption
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:282:CKN's localization generates cutoff error terms like:
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:293:- **Spatial Sobolev H¹(B_k) ↪ L⁶(B_k):** Standard embedding with constant independent of k (since B(1/2) ⊂ B_k ⊂ B(1)). Not optimal constant, but the same Sobolev exponent (6 in 3D) as CKN.
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:297:The **same Sobolev exponent** (L^6 in 3D, L^{10/3} in parabolic space-time) appears in both CKN and Vasseur, because both rely on the same 5-dimensional parabolic geometry. The critical exponent 10/3 (= 2·5/3) is universal to the parabolic Navier-Stokes system in R³×R and is not specific to either proof method.
