../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:3:**Goal:** Analyze Fanghua Lin's simplified proof (1998) of the CKN partial regularity theorem. Extract 5 structural features and compare with CKN (1982).
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:17:Lin works in exactly the same setting as CKN: suitable weak solutions (u, p) of 3D incompressible NS on a space-time domain Q ⊆ ℝ³ × ℝ, with the local energy inequality (LEI). The parabolic cylinders Q_r(z₀) = B_r(x₀) × (t₀ − r², t₀) and scale-invariant quantities are identical to CKN.
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:21:**The key structural choice:** Lin replaces CKN's direct quantitative energy estimates (explicit cutoff-function PDE estimates) with a **contradiction + compactness** argument. The proof is by contradiction: assuming a sequence of "almost-singular" points exists, Lin derives a contradiction by passing to a limit and using properties of the limiting solution.
