../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:45:    A(r) + E(r) + C(r) + D(r) < ε₀   ⟹   z₀ regular          ... (CKN-ε-REG)
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:55:The criterion C(r) + D(r) < ε₀ is therefore scale-invariant. Lin's criterion has the same scaling as CKN's — only the number of terms differs.
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:57:**Note on Lin's Theorem 1.2 (the main partial regularity statement):** Lin also states and proves the full P¹(Σ) = 0 result (his Theorem 1.2), using the same covering argument as CKN. The simplification is entirely in the ε-regularity step (Theorem 1.1), not in the covering step.
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:65:Lin's covering argument is **identical to CKN's**, with no structural modification.
