../../../../missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:86:   This gives a bound of the form ε₀ r_i ≤ C r_i^{5/10} × (constant) = C r_i^{1/2} × (constant), which by itself would give P^{1/2}(Σ) < ∞ — but this is the wrong approach. The actual CKN counting argument doesn't use this Hölder bound.
