../../../../missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:272:**No ε-absorption in the main iteration.** Unlike CKN (which uses Young's inequality with free ε to absorb gradient error terms from cutoffs), Vasseur's De Giorgi iteration uses **no free parameters in the core Proposition 3**. Every estimate is done with fixed universal constants. The only source of lossiness is:
