../../../../missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:293:- **Spatial Sobolev H¹(B_k) ↪ L⁶(B_k):** Standard embedding with constant independent of k (since B(1/2) ⊂ B_k ⊂ B(1)). Not optimal constant, but the same Sobolev exponent (6 in 3D) as CKN.
../../../../missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:297:The **same Sobolev exponent** (L^6 in 3D, L^{10/3} in parabolic space-time) appears in both CKN and Vasseur, because both rely on the same 5-dimensional parabolic geometry. The critical exponent 10/3 (= 2·5/3) is universal to the parabolic Navier-Stokes system in R³×R and is not specific to either proof method.
