../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-009-attacker-03.log:689:diff --git a/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md b/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-009-attacker-03.log:693:+++ b/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-03.md
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-009-attacker-03.log:701:+The problem is that the chain still overestimates what "exact packet structure" is likely to buy. Exact helical triad bookkeeping is real, but real is not the same as coercive. Waleffe-style interaction geometry, same-helicity suppression, and decimated-sector advantages have been around for a long time. The hard issue is not whether one can write a packet-complete ledger. The hard issue is whether any sign or exclusion effect survives full mixed-helicity completion, shell summation, localization, pressure restoration, and insertion into an LEI/CKN-facing endpoint. That is exactly where these ideas usually die.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-009-attacker-03.log:711:+- The candidate "bad transfer patterns" are not interchangeable. Comparable-scale stretching production, shell-bridging concentration feed, and similar targets sit at different levels of the problem. One might be natural in helical triad language while another is only natural on an LEI/CKN ledger. Letting the route pick whichever is most packet-friendly invites target shopping.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-009-attacker-03.log:751:+- The phrase "map the packet gain back to one physical-space endpoint line on the LEI / CKN ledger" hides a severe mismatch of levels. A packet gain can be exact and still fail to correspond to any sharp improvement on the local continuation bottlenecks that matter for beyond-De Giorgi.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-009-attacker-03.log:799:+The route starts in exact helical packet geometry and tries to finish on an LEI/CKN-style physical-space ledger. That is a major level mismatch. Unless the chain finds an unusually robust invariant that survives this translation, most symbolic gains will be spent before they reach the endpoint.
