../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-009-attacker-01.log:93:The clearest live mission lesson is still the SQG one: regularity did not come from beating the `beta = 4/3` Chebyshev ceiling, but from changing the drift-coupling mechanism. This chain is live only if one exact Navier-Stokes reformulation produces an estimate-level gain on one inherited LEI / CKN bottleneck that is not merely the old quadratic burden conjugated by projection, inversion, or a prettier variable.
