../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/final-decider.md:1:# Final Decider - beyond-de-giorgi / run-009
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/final-decider.md:10:- **Best execution fit:** the chain works directly on exact equations, localized debt, prior-art overlap, and LEI / CKN-facing insertion. That is the cleanest fit for an adversarial planning loop that needs honest kill conditions and reusable artifacts.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:7:The strongest version of the critique is not "this is obviously false." It is: the chain has not yet shown that there exists even one concrete reformulated unknown for 3D NS whose exact equation is structurally closer to SQG than to an LEI/CZ repackaging. Until that existence question is tightened up, the chain risks spending budget on elegant repackaging rather than on a genuinely Tao-sensitive mechanism.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:16:- The step forbids "prettier notation" rewrites of the LEI flux, but that filter is too weak. A reformulation can avoid looking like the old LEI while still being mathematically equivalent to the same quadratic bookkeeping after one inverse operator or one projection. The real exclusion test should be stronger: does the new variable produce an exact equation whose leading bad term is not merely the old nonlinearity conjugated by a singular integral?
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:17:- The endpoint choices are too coarse. "Localized regularity," "continuation criterion," and "concentration exclusion" have very different burdens. A commutator that helps in a continuation criterion may be useless for localization once cutoff commutators and pressure recovery are inserted. Freezing only the endpoint family does not prevent later goalpost shifting.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:50:- The phrase "benchmarked gain" is vague. Benchmarked against what? The De Giorgi 4/3 wall? A Serrin-type criterion? A CKN concentration measure? Without a frozen baseline scale and norm, Step 4 can overcount marginal algebraic improvements that do not move any theorem-facing threshold.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:74:The route is reformulation-first. That is both its novelty and its risk. Reformulation-heavy branches often generate exact equations with impressive-looking commutators and extension variables, only to discover that the nonlocal quadratic burden has merely moved. The chain does not contain a hard enough anti-repackaging criterion early enough in the process.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-02.md:109:This is one of the more serious chains in the run because it targets a genuine conceptual escape route rather than another incremental estimate. But it is still too loose where the mission is most vulnerable: candidate admission, anti-repackaging discipline, and early Tao calibration. As written, it is more likely to produce sophisticated reformulation theater than a real NS-specific mechanism. The honest prior should be obstruction, and the chain should be rewritten so that obstruction is reached quickly unless a very concrete exact unknown survives an unusually harsh early screen.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-008-judge-01.log:385:  endpoint family,
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/selector.md:39:- Chain 02 is the cleanest theorem-facing attempt to exploit the mission's explicit SQG lesson. It tests whether a changed variable package can produce a genuine commutator gain instead of another pressure or LEI repackaging.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The selected chain has a serious core idea: kill decorative reformulations early and force any surviving variable package to make contact with a theorem-facing bottleneck. That is a real strength. But the original version is still too discretionary in three places that matter: it freezes the setup too sharply and too early, it does not operationalize the burden ledger tightly enough, and it under-polices prior-art overlap and endpoint insertion debt.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The right repair is not to abandon the chain's anti-repackaging posture. It is to make the screening protocol more reproducible. The refined version should keep the demand for exact equations and endpoint contact, while allowing a small comparison slate, requiring a typed burden ledger, and forcing quantified gain-versus-debt accounting before any positive promotion.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:15:Terms such as "estimate-level gain," "same burden currency," and "decorative commutator" are directionally right but not yet decision-ready. The refined chain needs a typed burden ledger, an explicit admissible gain notion, and a rule for when currencies are comparable and when they are not.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:69:As a branch-specific heuristic, the mechanism-change premise is acceptable. This chain does not need to represent the whole mission. But the critique is right that the heuristic should be stated as a motivating bet, not as a procedural truth. The refined chain should allow the honest outcome that no reformulation outperforms the inherited old-variable burden ledger.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:76:2. Replace vague burden language with a typed burden ledger and an explicit comparability rule.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:82:8. Require a quantified or explicitly budgeted gain-versus-debt ledger inside the LEI / CKN insertion test.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-01.md:90:That probability is driven mostly by the chance of a clean obstruction memo or a narrow "no reformulation beats the inherited ledger" conclusion. A positive route remains possible, but only if one candidate survives both the quantified burden ledger and a non-cosmetic endpoint insertion test.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attack is directionally strong, but not uniformly correct. Its best points are that the original chain compresses too many distinct failure modes, understates how central the viscous and nonlocal obstacles are, and ties success too tightly to an inherited LEI / CKN-style proof interface. Its weakest move is to treat the whole chain as little more than a disguised demolition protocol. The original chain does contain real discipline: early admissibility gating, an explicit coercivity check, and a demand for a hard artifact are all good constraints.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-02.md:22:- The original chain treats "admits" too loosely for deformation-based observables on the suitable weak / LEI floor.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-02.md:23:- The Step 1 kill condition is too compressed; measurable definition, renormalized definition, approximation stability, and LEI-compatible compactness should be separated.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-02.md:60:- Keep the coercivity gate, but precede it with a ranked burden ledger and allow a compound-mechanism path when the controlled quantity is not the final bottleneck but plausibly feeds one.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-02.md:66:This is one of the attack's strongest points. The original chain does not just test whether the observable has value; it tests whether it can be inserted into one inherited LEI / CKN architecture. That is too narrow. Failure against that architecture is evidence, but not automatic proof that the mechanism itself is dead.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-02.md:151:- avoid treating inherited LEI / CKN insertion as the only legitimate theorem interface,
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-03.md:69:### 11. The endpoint mismatch between exact helical packet geometry and the LEI / CKN ledger is severe
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-009/judgments/chain-03.md:98:- The negative branch is strong. A sharp obstruction showing that completed helical gains are non-coercive, thin-sector, or too expensive to exchange into the LEI / CKN ledger is presentable.
