../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2492:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:181:The local energy inequality (LEI) integrated against φ gives (from CKN §2):
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2495:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:241:By the CKN pressure decomposition technique (see CKN §3, and Robinson-Rodrigo-Sadowski Ch.13 §13.3), p_2 is controlled by the non-local part of the pressure, which in turn is bounded by global L^{3/2} norms of u far from x₀.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2496:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:251:After establishing the local energy estimate, CKN run the following bootstrap:
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2500:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:397:**Young Step Y4: The absorption step in the CKN "pressure-regularity" lemma**
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2503:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:418:The key observation: **Y2 is the most significant lossy step.** The Ladyzhenskaya inequality with free parameter δ is where the proof is intentionally lossy — the power 3/2 of ||∇u||_{L²} in the vortex-stretching-type term forces a Young's inequality that introduces ν⁻³ or equivalent factors. In the *local* setting of CKN, the dissipation is sufficient to close (because the local energy inequality gives a uniform estimate), but the lossiness here is what prevents explicit computation of ε₀.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2504:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:427:1. Define suitable weak solutions (u,p) satisfying NS + local energy inequality (LEI)
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2508:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:507:**On the local energy inequality:** CKN Definition 2.2 and the discussion in §2. This inequality was first used by Scheffer (1976); CKN strengthened the partial regularity result by proving P¹(Σ) = 0 (Scheffer had only proven the time-Lebesgue measure of the singular set is zero).
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2509:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:515:**On Ladyzhenskaya-Seregin (1999):** They simplify the pressure decomposition step (avoiding the harmonic splitting p = p₁ + p₂ by working in a different functional framework), but the ε-regularity criterion and covering argument are identical to CKN.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2510:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:517:**On Robinson-Rodrigo-Sadowski (2016):** Their Chapter 13 presents the CKN proof in full, including the explicit form of the local energy inequality and the parabolic Sobolev embedding. Their §13.3 has the most explicit treatment of the pressure decomposition.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-005-explorer-001.log:2511:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md:521:**Verification note:** The precise form of (LEI-φ) — specifically the coefficient 2 in front of |∇u|² — appears in CKN (2.1). Some textbooks write the NS local energy inequality without the factor of 2 and with a different normalization of viscosity ν. With ν = 1 (CKN normalization), the factor is 2 (from 2ν = 2·1). Care is needed when comparing with papers that use ν explicitly.
