# Local Concentration Of Active Scales Is The Best Supported First Burden

Status: `INFERRED` best-supported burden with `VERIFIED` endpoint priority

For the Step-012 stochastic branch, the sharpest honest first burden on the
local record is `local concentration of active scales`.

Why this is the right filing:

- the active chain and judgment freeze `local concentration exclusion` as the
  default endpoint family;
- continuation remains a stricter fallback that is only admissible if the
  candidate observable already behaves like near-coercive norm control;
- and rival burden labels such as `vortex stretching growth` or `loss of
  control along advected filaments` stay at menu level rather than receiving
  the same endpoint priority.

So concentration is the best-supported first burden not because the repository
already proves a concentration mechanism, but because endpoint policy clearly
privileges it over the other burden menu entries.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-012-exploration-001-mechanism-family-scope-lock.md`

