-### Same-currency comparability rule
-
-- [PROPOSED] Two entries are comparable only if all of the following match:
-  `currency`, `compared object`, `stage`, `cutoff protocol`, `solution class`,
-  and `debt restoration status`.
-- [PROPOSED] A claimed improvement is same-currency only when it changes the
-  same typed object in the same stage. Examples:
-  - derivative-count on a pre-localization identity is **not** comparable to
-    derivative-count on the post-recovery LEI term;
-  - cancellation before cutoff insertion is **not** comparable to cancellation
-    after pressure recovery;
-  - compactness input is **not** comparable to coefficient shrinkage on
