+  the run-009 chain materials for endpoint-priority language; separated genuine
+  theorem endpoints from mechanism or bottleneck language; then reconciled the
+  active reformulation-audit branch with its inherited `I_flux[phi]` localized
+  LEI ledger.
+
+- Outcome:
+  succeeded narrowly.
+
+- One key takeaway:
+  the only genuinely frozen first theorem-facing window is local concentration
+  exclusion inside the inherited CKN/Lin epsilon-regularity contradiction
+  package, with later insertion tested against the fixed localized LEI cutoff-
+  flux bundle `I_flux[phi]`.
+
+- Frozen choices:
+  primary endpoint family:
+  `[VERIFIED]` `local concentration exclusion / endpoint-regularity exclusion`
+  on the inherited CKN/Lin LEI ledger.
+  backup endpoint family:
+  `[PROPOSED]` `conditional continuation / near-coercive norm-level control`,
+  reserve only.
+  solution class:
+  `[VERIFIED]` suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class with LEI.
+  localization regime:
+  `[VERIFIED]` one shared CKN-style parabolic cylinder, one standard smooth
+  cutoff, and one shared localized LEI package targeting `I_flux[phi]`.
+
+- Leads worth pursuing:
+  later Step-2 candidate packets should be tested only for estimate-level gain
+  on the fixed `I_flux[phi]` ledger;
+  continuation should be reopened only if a candidate already behaves like
+  near-coercive norm control on that same theorem floor.
