+## Scope-Lock Sheet
+
+| item | frozen choice | status | why it is admissibly frozen |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| primary endpoint family | `local concentration exclusion / endpoint-regularity exclusion on the inherited LEI / CKN ledger` | `[INFERRED]` | Run-009 requires one inherited theorem-facing endpoint on the suitable-weak / LEI floor, and the local record repeatedly privileges concentration exclusion as the honest first endpoint inside the CKN/Lin contradiction package |
+| backup endpoint family | `continuation / near-coercive norm-level control`, reserve only | `[INFERRED]` | The inherited record treats continuation as stricter than concentration exclusion and allows it only after norm-like behavior appears; this keeps exactly one harder reserve without reopening a menu |
+| theorem-facing baseline burden | full localized LEI cutoff-flux bundle `I_flux[phi] = ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇phi` under the shared CKN-style cutoff protocol | `[VERIFIED]` | This is the fixed bad term already frozen by the inherited exact-rewrite architecture and it is the unique place where localized nonlinear transport and pressure transport are charged together |
+| admissible gain notion | positive-margin smaller effective coefficient on the full `I_flux[phi]` bundle after pressure, commutator, reconstruction, and admissibility debt | `[VERIFIED]` | The exact-rewrite screening packet already fixes `coefficient shrinkage in the fixed localized LEI balance` as the only non-decorative gain currency |
+| typed burden ledger | derivative count, locality, cancellation, integrability, pressure recoverability, admissibility, compactness input, scaling compatibility | `[INFERRED]` | Each currency now has a fixed meaning relative to the same theorem-facing burden and later steps must post gains/debts into those explicit columns |
+| same-currency comparability rule | direct comparison only on the same full `I_flux[phi]` object, same solution class, same localization regime, and same charged debt | `[INFERRED]` | This blocks silent comparison between incomparable surrogate gains |
+| transfer-lemma rule | every cross-currency claim must explicitly imply a smaller full-bundle coefficient on `I_flux[phi]` after debt | `[INFERRED]` | Derivative, integrability, surrogate-cancellation, or compactness claims do not count until they are translated back to the frozen burden currency |
+| solution class | suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class with LEI | `[VERIFIED]` | This remains the only locally frozen theorem-facing floor on disk |
