-### Same-currency comparability rule
-
-- [PROPOSED] Two entries are comparable only if all of the following match:
-  `currency`, `compared object`, `stage`, `cutoff protocol`, `solution class`,
-  and `debt restoration status`.
-- [PROPOSED] A claimed improvement is same-currency only when it changes the
-  same typed object in the same stage. Examples:
-  - derivative-count on a pre-localization identity is **not** comparable to
-    derivative-count on the post-recovery LEI term;
-  - cancellation before cutoff insertion is **not** comparable to cancellation
-    after pressure recovery;
-  - compactness input is **not** comparable to coefficient shrinkage on
-    `I_flux[phi]`.
-- [PROPOSED] The only theorem-facing win condition is stricter still:
-  two packets are comparable for promotion only if both cash out to the same
-  localized LEI inequality with the same frozen bad term `I_flux[phi]`, and
-  one returns a strictly smaller net coefficient after the same debts are paid.
-
-### Mandatory transfer-lemma rule
-
-- [PROPOSED] A transfer lemma is mandatory whenever a claim crosses any one of
-  these boundaries:
-  - one currency to another;
-  - one stage to another;
-  - one object to another;
-  - candidate-native variables to the `(u,p)` LEI ledger;
-  - a surrogate term to the frozen bad term `I_flux[phi]`.
-- [PROPOSED] The lemma must be named and must state:
-  `source currency/object/stage`,
-  `target currency/object/stage`,
-  the hypotheses used,
-  the debts repaid during transfer,
-  and the exact theorem-facing inequality returned at the end.
-- [PROPOSED] Without that named lemma, the packet must be marked
-  `unresolved cross-currency claim` rather than credited as favorable.
-- [INFERRED] This rule is what blocks silent optimism from the most tempting
-  rewrite slogans:
-  derivative savings, prettier locality, NS-specific cancellation,
-  scale-invariant appearance, and compactness rhetoric all remain non-operative
-  until they are transferred back to the same frozen LEI coefficient language.
+- [VERIFIED] The baseline cash-out and the admissible gain notion are frozen in
