+# Receptionist Task - beyond-de-giorgi step-013
+
+Question:
+
+Identify the smallest repository-local source set that can support Chain Step 1
+for the active beyond-de-giorgi branch
+`Quantified Reformulation Audit With Anti-Repackaging, Early Endpoint Exchange,
+And Interface-Aware Budgeting`.
+
+I need exact file recommendations for all of the following:
+
+1. one primary endpoint family on the inherited LEI / CKN floor;
+2. one backup endpoint family only;
+3. one theorem-facing baseline burden and one admissible gain notion in that
+   burden language;
+4. one typed burden ledger with explicit currencies:
+   derivative count,
+   locality,
+   cancellation,
+   integrability,
+   pressure recoverability,
+   admissibility,
+   compactness input,
+   scaling compatibility;
+5. one same-currency comparability rule and one transfer-lemma rule for
+   cross-currency claims;
+6. one intended solution class and one localization regime;
+7. one anti-repackaging classifier with the three outputs
+   `equivalent redistribution`,
+   `ambiguous redistribution`,
+   `potentially live mechanism change`;
+8. one nearest-prior-art audit format naming the closest known reformulation
+   and the exact claimed mathematical delta.
+
